+{"id":"bd-rt5ms","title":"API Pagination & Filtering Utilities (Cursor-First)","description":"## Overview

Standardize how Flywheel Gateway parses and serves list endpoints:

- cursor-based pagination
- stable sorting
- filtering

The project already has canonical response envelopes via `sendList()` / `wrapList()` (including `hasMore` / `nextCursor` / `total`), but list endpoints still tend to implement query parsing ad-hoc.

## Goals

- A small, shared utility that:
  - parses `limit`, `cursor`, and optional `sort` safely
  - validates bounds (e.g., max page size)
  - produces a typed result that routes/services can use
- A consistent API surface:
  - list endpoints behave the same across the gateway
  - no more one-off cursor bugs (e.g., same-timestamp skips)

## Non-Goals

- Rewriting every endpoint at once.
- Introducing complex query DSLs (start small and pragmatic).

## Proposed Approach

1. Add `parseListQuery(c.req.query())` utility:
   - `limit` (default + max)
   - `cursor` (opaque)
   - `direction` / `sort` (optional)
2. Add helpers for cursor encoding/decoding (if not already present) and document the invariants.
3. Migrate a few high-value endpoints first (agents, history, jobs, audit).
4. Update OpenAPI descriptions for list endpoints (document query params consistently).

## Test Plan

- Unit: query parsing edge cases (NaN, negative, too-large, invalid cursor).
- Integration: list endpoints return stable pagination metadata.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] At least 3 list endpoints use the shared utility.
- [ ] OpenAPI consistently documents list query params.
- [ ] Cursor pagination is stable under identical timestamps/ids.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-01T05:22:52.147374472Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-01T05:22:52.168085453Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["api","backend"]}
